erceived and interpr=\r\neted by another mind. This translation is dependent on one&#39;s mental conditi=\r\noning. Thus, what we perceive at the end is conformant to our own mental co=\r\nnditioning!\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; Suppose a foolish person thought while praying to an i=\r\ndol everyday of a fierce goddess who kills all of one&#39;s enemies, brings peo=\r\nple under one&#39;s control and makes one successful. Suppose you focus on that=\r\n idol. Then you are susceptible to that kind of thoughts. However, if you s=\r\nee her as someone who helps you overcome your weaknesses and become dispass=\r\nionate, nothing bad is going to happen to you. But the fact that someone us=\r\ned that idol as a repository of negative thoughts becomes a minor obstructi=\r\non.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; However, please note that this principle works without an idol=\r\n too. Suppose someone goes to a particular place (e.g. a church bench) and =\r\nprays to god with certain desires/thoughts everyday. Those thoughts are pre=\r\nsent in the air there. Anyone praying there later may be a little susceptib=\r\nle to such thoughts. The concentration of thoughts may be a little higher w=\r\nhen an idol serves as a repository as opposed to just air. That&#39;s all.\n&gt; &gt; =\r\n\n&gt; &gt; However, please note that most people have some devotion, some surrend=\r\ner, some love and some fear of wrong-doing when they are praying to god, wi=\r\nthin or without an idol. Thus, any negative and selfish thoughts are also a=\r\nccompanied by a lot of desirable thoughts. Thus, the downside I mentioned i=\r\ns not a big deal. This downside becomes considerable only in rare cases of =\r\nreally taamasik sadhakas indulging in terrible practices without understand=\r\ning what they are doing.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; is Idol worship risky?\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; Bottoml=\r\nine is that I do not see any risk in idol worship.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; * * *\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; =\r\n&gt; Does Man create God, or God creates man?\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; God created man as his =\r\nreplica. But the replica got corrupted with time. Now, man needs to recreat=\r\ne god in his mind and fill the mind with god, so that he can go back to the=\r\n source and become free from this cycle. But, due to the corruptions/ condi=\r\ntioning of the mind, he is not able to create god correctly. He ends up cre=\r\nating god as a replica of his current corrupt state! The goal is to keep cr=\r\neating god in mind and keep refining him and hence keep refining oneself an=\r\nd eventually become pure. When one is pure and creates god as a replica of =\r\noneself, that god will match the god that created man in the first place. W=\r\nhen that god fills one&#39;s mind, one is free from the cycle.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; * * *\n&gt;=\r\n &gt; \n&gt; &gt; I saw people deviating and speaking disrespectfully about respected=\r\n spiritual leaders of other religions.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; In general, please remember=\r\n that saying negative things about people that one may not have understood =\r\nfully or correctly is unwise.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; From time to time, the Lord may send=\r\n someone to a part of the world to maintain the correct balance of dharma a=\r\nnd adhrama that is required in that part of the world at that time. One can=\r\nnot judge a yogi or spiritual teacher based on how many misdeeds were done =\r\nby people claiming to follow that person. Worse things may have happened if=\r\n god did not send that person! If some people following a yogi or spiritual=\r\n teacher attained some level of realization, it means something. Let us not=\r\n be harsh in judging people we have not met physically or otherwise.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt;=\r\n &gt; If one is unhappy because of misdeeds committed by people claiming to a =\r\nfollow a yogi or spiritual teacher, that may be justified. But, Nature will=\r\n correct things and change the equilibrium from time and time. Leave things=\r\n to Nature and do your part by doing sadhana. In fact, my firm belief is th=\r\nat we are on the cusp of a big change in the equilibrium at many levels.\n&gt; =\r\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Best regards,\n&gt; &gt; Narasimha\n&gt; &gt; ------------ --------- --------- ---=\r\n------ --------- --------- -\n&gt; &gt; Do a Short Homam Yourself: http://www.Vedi=\r\ncAst rologer.org/ homam\n&gt; &gt; Do Pitri Tarpanas Yourself: http://www.VedicAst=\r\n rologer.org/ tarpana\n&gt; &gt; Spirituality: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/ved=\r\nic- wisdom\n&gt; &gt; Free Jyotish lessons (MP3): http://vedicastro. home.comcast.=\r\n net\n&gt; &gt; Free Jyotish software (Windows): http://www.VedicAst rologer.org\n&gt;=\r\n &gt; Jyotish writings: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/JyotishWri tings\n&gt; &gt; S=\r\nri Jagannath Centre (SJC) website: http://www.SriJagan nath.org\n&gt; &gt; -------=\r\n----- --------- --------- --------- --------- --------- - \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; ----- O=\r\nriginal Message ----- \n&gt; &gt; From: rajarshi nandy \n&gt; &gt; To: vedic-wisdom@ yaho=\r\nogroups. com \n&gt; &gt; Sent: Thursday, October 08, 2009 2:38 PM\n&gt; &gt; Subject: Re:=\r\n [vedic-wisdom] Re: Holy Places\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; Namaste,\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; To add to m=\r\ny query, a good number of religions explicitly prohibit idol worship. If th=\r\ne underlying truth is one, how can it be so contradictory? \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; I can =\r\nunderstand that a Idol may contain a presence created by human imagination =\r\nwhich maynot have a divine link. Not everybody is a Ramakrishna who can act=\r\nually call Mahakali into an Idol.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; But then, what ever the idol may=\r\n contain, postive/negative/ creative/ destruction, if someone prays to it w=\r\nith devotion, assuming that it is reaching God, is it not enough? After all=\r\n God is finally tax collecter of prayers. Does not all prayer finally reach=\r\n God, irrespective of whether a divine presence is there o