 minor obstruction.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &=\r\ngt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; However, please note that this principle works without an=\r\n idol too. Suppose someone goes to a particular place (e.g. a church bench)=\r\n and prays to god with certain desires/thoughts everyday. Those thoughts ar=\r\ne present in the air there. Anyone praying there later may be a little susc=\r\neptible to such thoughts. The concentration of thoughts may be a little hig=\r\nher when an idol serves as a repository as opposed to just air. That&#39;s all.=\r\n&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; However, please note that most people have some=\r\n devotion, some surrender, some love and some fear of wrong-doing when they=\r\n are praying to god, within or without an idol. Thus, any negative and self=\r\nish thoughts are also accompanied by a lot of desirable thoughts. Thus, the=\r\n downside I mentioned is not a big deal. This downside becomes considerable=\r\n only in rare cases of really taamasik sadhakas indulging in terrible\n prac=\r\ntices without understanding what they are doing.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n &gt; is Idol worship risky?&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Bottomline is that =\r\nI do not see any risk in idol worship.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; * * *&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; Does Man create God, or God creates man?&lt;BR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; God created man as his replica. But the replica got c=\r\norrupted with time. Now, man needs to recreate god in his mind and fill the=\r\n mind with god, so that he can go back to the source and become free from t=\r\nhis cycle. But, due to the corruptions/ conditioning of the mind, he is not=\r\n able to create god correctly. He ends up creating god as a replica of his =\r\ncurrent corrupt state! The goal is to keep creating god in mind and keep re=\r\nfining him and hence keep refining oneself and eventually become pure. When=\r\n one is pure and creates god as a replica of oneself, that god will match t=\r\nhe god that created man in the first place. When that god fills\n one&#39;s mind=\r\n, one is free from the cycle.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; * * *&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; I saw people deviating and speaking disrespectfully about re=\r\nspected spiritual leaders of other religions.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; In=\r\n general, please remember that saying negative things about people that one=\r\n may not have understood fully or correctly is unwise.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt; From time to time, the Lord may send someone to a part of the world =\r\nto maintain the correct balance of dharma and adhrama that is required in t=\r\nhat part of the world at that time. One cannot judge a yogi or spiritual te=\r\nacher based on how many misdeeds were done by people claiming to follow tha=\r\nt person. Worse things may have happened if god did not send that person! I=\r\nf some people following a yogi or spiritual teacher attained some level of =\r\nrealization, it means something. Let us not be harsh in judging people we h=\r\nave not met physically or otherwise.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;\n &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; If one is =\r\nunhappy because of misdeeds committed by people claiming to a follow a yogi=\r\n or spiritual teacher, that may be justified. But, Nature will correct thin=\r\ngs and change the equilibrium from time and time. Leave things to Nature an=\r\nd do your part by doing sadhana. In fact, my firm belief is that we are on =\r\nthe cusp of a big change in the equilibrium at many levels.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;B=\r\nR&gt;&gt; &gt; Best regards,&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; ------------ =\r\n--------- --------- --------- --------- --------- -&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Do a Short=\r\n Homam Yourself: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/homam&quot; rel=3Dnof=\r\nollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://www.VedicAst rologer.org/ homam&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; 